        <!-- Slide 4: How It's Made -->
        <div class="slide">
            <h2>How Sopa Paraguaya is Made</h2>
            <div class="slide-content">
                <div class="slide-img-container">
                    <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/81/Sopa_Paraguaia_e_Chipa_%28cropped%29.jpg/640px-Sopa_Paraguaia_e_Chipa_%28cropped%29.jpg" alt="Preparation of Sopa Paraguaya" class="slide-img">
                </div>
                <p class="attribution">Image source: <em>Sopa Paraguaia e Chipa (cropped).jpg</em>, Flavio Andre/MTur, MTur Destinos, Creative Commons Zero, Public Domain Dedication, via Wikimedia Commons.</p>
                <ol class="procedure-list">
                    <li>Saut茅 onions until golden brown</li>
                    <li>Mix corn flour, milk, eggs, and cheese together</li>
                    <li>Add the saut茅ed onions to the mixture</li>
                    <li>Pour the batter into a greased baking dish</li>
                    <li>Bake until golden and cooked through</li>
                    <li>Let it cool slightly before serving</li>
                </ol>
            </div>
